## Examples

### Command line

~~~
$ ign gui -l
/home/louise/plugins/
└── No plugins
/home/louise/.ignition/gui/plugins
├── libhello_plugin.so
└── libhello_plugin2.so
/usr/local/lib/ign-gui-0/plugins
└── libImageDisplay.so
~~~

### Window

content.raw: Only the first one is listed and can be loaded. The precedence order is listed in the README. Basically, if you want to override an "official" plugin, just use the same name and add the path to `IGN_GUI_PLUGIN_PATH`.
content.html: Only the first one is listed and can be loaded. The precedence order is listed in the README. Basically, if you want to override an "official" plugin, just use the same name and add the path to IGN_GUI_PLUGIN_PATH.
